latestIgtvVideos.title: 😷THIS IS IT! I AM DONE💭
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I weigh 80kgs.

It’s hard to start from bottom all over again, it’s harder when you hold a position where people look upto you for motivation, when you have an accountability.

Today where I stand is not a position about which you can post, influencers normally don’t post this side of themselves. You normally lose followers when you don’t stay up.
And I did lose a lot of followers because of this. I fell hard, from 120k to 105k followers today. Though these numbers are not my motivation, but you become a social media influencer because of these numbers only.

This is not the brighter side of this industry.

But anyways, this happened in the past few months & I hold no regrets about anything.

Sharing with you all my downside today. I think most of you will relate to my situation. I don’t blame the pandemic for this, this is what I chose.

Most of you all think of the day when you’d start, when to start, how to start, take this as a sign to start!

People who take me as their motivation and relate with me, come on guys! Let’s do it together!

Today is my Day 1 of the journey. 
It’s hard to start from bottomToday is the day when I give myself a new beginning, new goal. 

Lastly, I am grateful & blessed. Thankyou @prosupps @prosupps @ceo_swole @arjun.kumra @humanhealthstore @lesliefranko for staying with me. Let’s reach heights together. & a special thankyou to those who stayed with me on social media too and did not unfollow me . 😜

latestIgtvVideos.title: Discipline vs Motivation!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
-
Motivation is “Why to Do”

Motivation is the why behind the goal.  It’s your little engine that says you can, when the rest of you says you can’t.

It’s also the same force that can help you move mountains, on a good day.

Motivation is a life-long skill that you can improve through self-awareness and proven strategies.  The better you know your own drivers and levers, the more effective you’ll be at getting the results you want in your life.

Discipline is “What to Do”

Then there’s self-discipline.  Self-discipline is the ability to correct your behavior (Self-discipline is simply correcting or regulating your behavior for the sake of improvement.

Will is based on thinking and reason to create action – motivation is more from emotion.) It helps you get back on your course when you fall off your path.

It helps you do the right thing in the moment for your long-term benefit, when you may want to do something else. “Only the disciplined are truly free.  The undisciplined are slaves to moods, appetites, and passions.” Self-discipline is a muscle that gets stronger the more you flex it.

So, In this #COVID_19 pandemic the only thing that will keep us on track and move closer to our goal is DISCIPLINE!

You gotta choose Discipline over Motivation.

latestPosts.caption:
This journey was never meant to be this emotional.
I flew to Vietnam to surprise my sister after 3 years. And I did. We laughed, we lived those missed years again.

Then everything shifted.
My father fell seriously unwell back home.
I wasn’t there. In that moment, my friend—more like a God-sent brother—stepped in within 5 minutes and handled everything with strength and care he did what even I couldn’t have. My family was there🤲🏻
At the same time, theft happened at the immigration in Ho Chi Minh—money gone, mind scattered.

I took the longest 24-hour journey of my life, filled with anxiety and helplessness.
But when I reached, my father was better. My people were there.

God didn’t just guide me—He placed the right people where I couldn’t be.
What started as a joyful reunion became a powerful reminder:
I am protected. I am blessed. I am never alone.

#EmotionalRide #GratefulHeart #GodsPlan #FamilyOverEverything #StrengthInStruggle #friendslikefamily #gratitude #pranavSaini #blessedandhighlyfavored #PranavSaini
